WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
That's the OSCE grader, just with a different face on it.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:07.000
That's what the NBME did. It's not just me, right?

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:09.000
It's the state of Kentucky. It's my students.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:13.000
And because we found that we had lightning in a bottle,

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.000
we had lightning in a bottle with these guys,

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.000
because I was in the room and I got to design
our AI literacy course.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.000
I built the whole thing around what they achieved, right?

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:26.000
So every single module is a new practical skill

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.000
that you have to use in order to build
a longitudinal project.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.000
We call it the Bluegrass AI proposal.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Students have to choose a problem in a community
that they care about

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:41.000
and try to solve it with artificial intelligence.
And so what you get is Shayla McGuire.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:48.000
She's a 19-year-old kid. She built a system to help
her sorority raise money for their philanthropy,

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:54.000
which is a shelter for people who are survivors
of domestic abuse. Right?

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:59.000
And she raised thousands of dollars. That's the OSCE grader.
It's just got a different face.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:06.000
It's just got a different purpose, right?
All of this came from the NBME.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:10.612
And so this is where I want to slow down a little bit,
because what it's doing for Kentucky now is actually making a difference.
